---
description: Frontend Next.js and React conventions for BetAgent apps.
globs:
  - "apps/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Default to React Server Components. Add `"use client"` only when interactivity (`useState`, `useEffect`, browser APIs, drag/drop, etc.) justifies bundling logic to the browser.
- Follow App Router primitives: colocate routes under `app/`, expose `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` per subtree requirements.

### Package imports

- UI primitives originate from `@repo/ui` (already-wrapped shadcn exports).
- Reusable compositions live in `@repo/components`.
- Hooks/utilities/session glue live in `@repo/core`.
- Every GraphQL document must import typed hooks/selectors strictly from `@repo/graphql`.
- Do not stash bespoke widgets inside `@repo/ui`.

### Data and forms

- Use generated hooks/selectors exported by `@repo/graphql`; never interpolate ad-hoc query strings inline in JSX.
- Wire forms with react-hook-form + zod schemas via `@hookform/resolvers/zod` and colocate schemas in `<feature>.schemas.ts` near the owning form folder.

### Security and authentication

- Call `auth()`/`getServerSession` helpers from server components/route handlers whenever reading protected props.
- Client components consume `useSession` only after ensuring data was already guarded server-side.
- Keep CSP nonce middleware plus secure headers (`X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`) enabled globally.
